to the editor i read with increasing dismay your article about donna moffett a new teacher at public school 92 in brooklyn tears yes but triumphs too for a teacher front page dec 11 to put any new teacher particularly one without sufficient training into a first grade class borders on malpractice these young children from varied backgrounds need someone with the knowledge and experience to create a literacy environment in the classroom the greatest resources a school district has should be used at the earliest levels to teach young children the pleasures of learning nothing takes the place of an experienced successful early childhood teacher lissa fine loudonville ny dec 11 2000 the writer is a retired teacher

